Reset the hardware/software implementing the AMB interface. This command will cause the hardware implementing the AMB interface (typically and AMBSI-or AMBSI-2) to reset in a fashion that is equivalent having detected a reset signal on the AMB. Once this command is received the AMB interface may ignore AMB communications for up to 1 second.
Send a reset pulse to the hardware device attached to the AMB. This command will cause the a signal to be asserted that can be used to trigger a reset in the hardware attached to the AMB interface.
